Business Brief -- Chrysler Corp.:
   Firm's Variable-Fuel Cars
   Won't Cost Buyers Extra
Chrysler said it will begin selling only 2,000 of these
variable-fuel cars in California this summer. Chrysler said
production potentially could reach 100,000 in the 1994 model
years.
   California regulators have said that Ford Motor Co. has
promised to build 200 variable-fuel vans by early next year,
and to produce another 2,500 variable-fuel midsize Tauruses
after October 1992.